====Currency units====
Select the main [[Main/en/Currency|currency unit]] for the game.

====Distance units====
Select the distance units to Imperial (miles) or Metric (kilometers).

====Road vehicles====
Select the side of the road that road vehicles drive on, and which side of the track signals appear on.

====Town names====
Select which country [[Main/en/town names]] are from in randomly generated games.

To select a grf town name generator, please add the grf at the "[[Main/en/NewGRF]]" on the main screen first.

====Autosave====
Select how often to save the game just in case it crashes or you want to revert back. [[Main/en/Autosave|Autosaves]] will appear in the save\autosave\ directory.

====Language====
Select the [[Main/en/language]] used for the interface.

====Screen resolution====
Select the [[Main/en/Resolution|screen resolution]] in full screen mode or the window size in window mode.

====Screenshot format====
Select the [[Main/en/screenshot format]].

====Base graphics set====
Select the base graphics to use in case of multiple sources like [[Main/en/Installation FAQ#What files do I need from TTD.3F|DOS, Windows]] and [[Main/en/Graphics Replacement|OpenGFX]].

====Base sounds set====
Select the base sound to use in case of multiple sources like [[Main/en/Installation FAQ#What files do I need from TTD.3F|original]] and [[Main/en/Sound Effects Replacement|OpenSFX]].

====Base music set====
Select the base music set to use in case of multiple sources like [[Main/en/Installation FAQ#What files do I need from TTD.3F|TTD]], [[Main/en/OpenMSX]] or [[Main/en/Scott Joplin Anthology]]. Unlike other basesets, this can be changed in game.

